    localDesignerCulturePara: "Chicago designer culture operates out of the Merchandise Mart and LuxeHome on the 1st and 2nd floors. NKBA Chicago Midwest chapter designers charge 12-18% of project. Mick De Giulio defines the Chicago luxury standard. Mid-market homeowners lean on Airoom, Normandy Remodeling, and MK Bros for design-build. The Chicago Architecture Center hosts a strong bungalow and Prairie-style preservation community that influences period-correct kitchen detailing.",
    applianceUpsellPara: "Abt Electronics in Glenview is the single largest appliance retailer in the metro and dominates spec on most North Shore remodels. Grand Appliance, Sears Outlet, and regional Ferguson branches fill out the delivery network. Thermador and Wolf dominate the upper-middle spec; GE Cafe and KitchenAid commercial-series cover the bungalow-belt upsell. Induction is slower to penetrate than coastal markets because Peoples Gas rates remain attractive and winter outage risk motivates dual-fuel choices.",
    historicDistrictConstraintsPara: "Chicago Landmarks-designated districts include the Bungalow Belt (honorary district but not formal), Lincoln Park, Old Town Triangle, Prairie Avenue, and the Pullman National Monument. Any exterior visible kitchen work (hood vent on front of house, enlarged window) requires Commission on Chicago Landmarks review. Oak Park and Evanston have their own preservation commissions with different rules; Evanston requires approval for any alteration visible from the public way.",
