    permitTimelinePara: "Houston ProjectDox runs 1-3 business days on residential kitchen permits, making it one of the fastest major-city permit portals in the country. Surrounding Harris County (unincorporated), Sugar Land, Pearland, and The Woodlands each have separate portals with varying turnaround. Deed-restricted neighborhoods in River Oaks, Memorial Villages, and West U add private architectural review that runs another 2-6 weeks and often requires committee meetings with specific submission dates.",
    localDesignerCulturePara: "Houston designer culture centers on the Houston Design Center and the Decorative Center Houston near Washington Avenue. IIDA Texas Gulf Coast chapter designers charge 12-18% of project. Eleanor Cummings and Garrett Hunter define the traditional-luxury River Oaks aesthetic. Mid-market homeowners use Re-Bath, Kitchen Tune-Up franchises, and design-build firms including BuildFBG and Hann Builders for project delivery on 60-120 day schedules.",
    applianceUpsellPara: "Thermador and Wolf dominate Memorial and River Oaks spec; Frigidaire Professional and GE Monogram fill out the upper-middle Heights and West U market. Appliance Distributors in Houston Heights, Boyd Appliance in Katy, and regional Ferguson branches deliver most jobs. Gas remains dominant because CenterPoint Energy gas rates are low and grid resilience concerns after Winter Storm Uri (2021) made homeowners actively avoid all-electric builds. Induction is a coastal-style preference not yet widespread.",
